info.headline: High Wind Warning issued December 15 at 11:57AM CST until December 16 at 9:00AM CST by NWS GreenBay
info.description: ...DENSE FOG ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 9 PM CST THIS EVENING... ...HIGH WIND WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 9 PM THIS EVENING TO 9 AM CST THURSDAY... * WHAT...For the High Wind Warning, southwest winds 20 to 30 mph with gusts up to 55 mph expected. For the Dense Fog Advisory, visibility one quarter mile or less in dense fog. * WHERE...Langlade, Lincoln, Oneida, Vilas, Florence, Forest, Menominee, Northern Marinette County and Northern Oconto County Counties. * WHEN...For the High Wind Warning, from 9 PM this evening to 9 AM CST Thursday. For the Dense Fog Advisory, until 9 PM CST this evening. * IMPACTS...Damaging winds will blow down trees and power lines. Some power outages are expected. Travel will be difficult, especially for high profile vehicles. Low visibility could make driving conditions hazardous in dense fog.
info.instruction: Remain in the lower levels of your home during the windstorm, and avoid windows. Watch for falling debris and tree limbs. Use caution if you must drive. If driving, slow down, use your headlights, and leave plenty of distance ahead of you.
